# Node.js Utilities

The node package contains utility functions that are designed to work in Node.js environments and may use Node.js-specific APIs.

## Key Files

- [writeJson.js](mdc:packages/node/writeJson.js): Utility for writing JSON data to files
- [readFileAsJson.ts](mdc:packages/node/readFileAsJson.ts): Utility for reading JSON data from files
- [exec.js](mdc:packages/node/exec.js): Wrapper for executing shell commands
- [git.js](mdc:packages/node/git.js): Git-related utilities
- [invariant.ts](mdc:packages/node/invariant.ts): Assertion utility for runtime checks
- [simpleServer.js](mdc:packages/node/simpleServer.js): Simple HTTP server implementation
- [serve.js](mdc:packages/node/serve.js): More feature-rich server implementation
- [colorful-terminal-message.js](mdc:packages/node/colorful-terminal-message.js): Utilities for colorful terminal output

## Sub-directories

- [cli/](mdc:packages/node/cli): Command-line interface utilities
- [jwt/](mdc:packages/node/jwt): JSON Web Token utilities

## Dependencies

This package depends on:
- [chalk](mdc:packages/node/package.json): For colorful terminal output
- [zod](mdc:packages/node/package.json): For runtime type validation
